    - The else if statement will check its own condition and either run or skip its
      code depending on whether or not the condition is true. Write an else if statement
      after an if statement and before an else statement.
    - "~if(condition1)\r`\n~{\r`\n~  //runs if condition1 is true\r`\n~}`"
    - "~else if(condition2)\r`\n~{\r`\n~  //runs if condition1 is false & condition2
